place.name: WATERDEN
place.gazetteerText: WATERDEN, a parish in Docking district, Norfolk; 3 miles WSW of Walsingham r. station. Post town, Fakenham. Acres, 763. Real property, £1,026. Pop., 44. Houses, 4. The property belongs to the Earl of Leicester. The living is a rectory, annexed to Egmere. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
